法規內容.條文內容:
Upon receiving the application for establishment application and license renewal of satellite broadcasting businesses and foreign satellite broadcasting businesses, the National Communications Commission (hereinafter referred to as the Commission) shall review the application and operation plan in accordance with the provisions of Article 1, Articles 4 through 8, and Paragraph 1, Article 18 of the Act, as well as Articles 7 through 9 of the Administrative Procedure Act. The review of license renewal application shall take the following items into account:
1. Operational implementation reports, evaluation results, and the corrective situation after evaluation;
2. Records of violating the Act;
3. Records of infringing the rights of others through broadcasted programs and advertisements;
4. Management of subscriber disputes;
5. Financial status; and
6. Other items sufficient enough to affect operations.
For those applications for establishment and license renewal of the satellite broadcasting businesses and foreign satellite broadcasting businesses in the previous paragraph that fall under one of the circumstances stipulated in Article 9, Paragraphs 1 and 2, Article 10, or Article 19 of the Act, the Commission shall reject their applications with the reasons stated.
